.TH "named_prepare_buf" 9 "named_prepare_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
named_prepare_buf \- allocate & initialize a publication message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sk_buff *" named_prepare_buf
.BI "(struct net *net "  ","
.BI "u32 type "  ","
.BI "u32 size "  ","
.BI "u32 dest "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
the associated network namespace
.IP "type" 12
message type
.IP "size" 12
payload size
.IP "dest" 12
destination node
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The buffer returned is of size INT_H_SIZE + payload size
